Remove the @sirloin steak{12%ounce} from the #fridge{} and allow it to come to room temperature. Meanwhile, core, seed and remove the white ribs from the @green bell pepper{1}, then thinly slice into strips. Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}. Thinly slice the @scallions{2}(whites and greens separated). Very finely slice or mince the scallion greens. Zest and halve the @lemon{1}. Finely chop the @cilantro{1%bunch}.

In a #small pot{}, bring @water{1%cup} to a boil with a pinch of @salt{}. Add the @couscous{1/2%cup}, cover, and remove from heat until the rest of the meal is ready.

Meanwhile, heat @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add the bell pepper and cook, tossing, for ~{5%minutes}, until softened. Add the scallion whites and garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}, until fragrant. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} and set aside in a #medium bowl{}.

Season the steak on all sides with @cumin{1%tablespoon}, salt and pepper. Heat another @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in the same #pan{} over high heat. Add the steak to the pan and cook ~{4-6%minutes} per side, or until cooked to desired doneness. Set aside to rest for ~{5%minutes}.

Toss the couscous, @spinach{1%bunch}, and lemon zest together with the bell pepper mixture. Season with salt and pepper.

Make the scallion chimichurri: in a #small bowl{}, combine the cilantro, scallion greens, @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, and a squeeze of lemon. Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff the couscous with a fork. Thinly slice the steak against the grain, then serve on a bed of couscous salad. Top with cilantro-scallion chimichurri and enjoy!